  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "Command injection in paddle.utils.download._wget_download (bypass filter) in paddlepaddle/paddle 2.6.0\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2024-0815 is a command injection vulnerability in PaddlePaddle's download utility, affecting the PaddlePaddle software framework. PaddlePaddle is a general-purpose AI framework; the flaw resides in its software supply chain (a dependency used to build/train/deploy AI systems). It's a security vulnerability with high impact, meeting AVID criteria for AI-related, GP AI supply-chain, and evidence-based assessment."
